721245f-a.text:
Madison Avenue, S.W. corner of 27th Street, showing New York Jockey
Club House, demolished before 1V10.
Ne view is west on 27th Street. The arch shown st the left of the picture is part of Madison Scuare Garden (1890-1925). The small buildings on 27th Street between the Jockey Club and the newly erected Brunswick Building are old stables; in a few more years
they will begin giving way to office buildings.
Probably about 1907.
Brown Brothers, Photographers.

721247f-a.text: Madison Avenue, west side, between 27th and 28th streets, showing new office buildings Nos. 72-76. The two story (Nott) Memorial Library, shown in part on the left, and the Columbus Apartments Hotel, the building with fire escape, will be demolished between 1915-16 to build Madison Avenue wing of Prince George Hotel.

721243f-a.text:
Madison Avenue, east side, at E. 27th Street, showing unknown (to the writer) individuals leaving the old Madison Square Garden (right). The photographer is wiewing northeastward to show at the left buildings on the north side of E. 27th Street to the

prior to 1923.

721248f-a.text:
63-71 Madison Avenue, east side, from 27th Street about halfway to 28th Street, showing a new office building 65-7 Madison Avenue,
nearing completion. It replaces two small houses.
Notice that Madison Avenue is temporarily a one-way street.
1923.
Dnift of E. M. Jenke.
